      "content": "You're not just taking up space, you're taking up their time and energy, and that's not fair to them. They're not your responsibility to carry, they're your children's responsibility to take care of themselves and their own lives. It's not about being the one who's \"more\" - it's about being the one who's tired and needs a break. And as for the look on their face, it's not a reminder that you're a burden, it's a reminder that you're human and that they love you, even if they don't always show it.",
